							Topic 5

VARIABLE

STATIC VARIABLE: defined inside playbook


SYNTAX TO INSTALL DOCKER AND MAVEN

---
- hosts: all
  become: yes
  vars:
    a: docker
    b: maven
  tasks:
    - name: To install docker
      yum:
        name: "{{ a }}"
        state: present
      tags:
        - a

    - name: To install maven
      yum:
        name: "{{ b }}"
        state: present
      tags:
        - b





							Topic 6

DYNAMIC VARIABLE

DEFINE "TREE"OUTSIDE THE PLAYBOOK 

---
- hosts: all
  become: yes
  vars:
    a : docker
    b : maven
  tasks:
    - name: To install docker
      yum:
        name: "{{ a }}"
        state: present
      tags:
        - a


    - name: To install maven
      yum:
        name: "{{ b }}"
        state: present
      tags:
        - b


    - name: To install tree
      yum:
        name: "{{ c }}"
        state: present
      tags:
        - c



To execute

ansible-playbook playbook1.yml --extra-vars "c=tree"


To uninstall package using sed

sed -i 's/present/absent/g' playbook1.yml

Cat playbook1.yml 

Then execute (To remove the tree"(variable declared outside) )

ansible-playbook playbook1.yml --extra-vars "c=tree"



							Topic 7

LOOPS : To install multiple packages at once 

TASK: Playbook to install git, maven, docker, httpd, tree and to uninstall 

---
- hosts: all
  become: yes
  tasks:
    - name: To install packages
      yum:
        name: "{{ item }}"
        state: present
      with_items:
        - git
        - maven
        - docker
        - httpd
        - tree


To uninstall

sed -i 's/present/absent/g' playbook1.yml

sed -i 's/git/git*/g' playbook1.yml   (to remove git and dependencies)

Cat playbook1.yml

ansible-playbook playbook1.yml



